      • setInputPattern

        public void setInputPattern​(int pattern)
        Sets an input pattern of the text box.
        Parameters:
        pattern - Indicates the input pattern to set. Available options are as follows: EditorAttribute#PATTERN_NULL EditorAttribute#PATTERN_TEXT EditorAttribute#PATTERN_NUMBER EditorAttribute#PATTERN_PHONE EditorAttribute#PATTERN_DATETIME EditorAttribute#PATTERN_URI EditorAttribute#PATTERN_EMAIL, EditorAttribute#PATTERN_PASSWORD.

      • setEnterKeyType

        public void setEnterKeyType​(int type)
        Sets a key type of the text box.
        Parameters:
        type - Indicates the key type to set. For example, to search after pressing the Enter key, set this parameter to EditorAttribute#ENTER_KEY_TYPE_SEARCH. Available options are as follows: EditorAttribute#ENTER_KEY_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED EditorAttribute#ENTER_KEY_TYPE_SEARCH EditorAttribute#ENTER_KEY_TYPE_GO EditorAttribute#ENTER_KEY_TYPE_SEND EditorAttribute#ENTER_KEY_TYPE_DONE EditorAttribute#ENTER_KEY_TYPE_NEXT EditorAttribute#ENTER_KEY_TYPE_PREVIOUS.
        Since:
        3

      • setInputOption

        public void setInputOption​(int option)
        Sets the text box action.
        Parameters:
        option - Indicates the information about the text box action to set. The value can be any of the following constants or the bitwise inclusive OR result of any two of the following constants: EditorAttribute#OPTION_NONE EditorAttribute#OPTION_MULTI_LINE EditorAttribute#OPTION_AUTO_CAP_CHARACTERS EditorAttribute#OPTION_AUTO_CAP_WORDS EditorAttribute#OPTION_AUTO_CAP_SENTENCES EditorAttribute#OPTION_NO_FULLSCREEN EditorAttribute#OPTION_ASCII For example, EditorAttribute#OPTION_NONE | EditorAttribute#OPTION_MULTI_LINE.
        Since:
        3
